    "/v2/application_mappings/find_by_cpe_mappings": {
      "get": {
        "summary": "CPE mappings by vendor and product",
        "description": "\n<p>\n  Returns Common Platform Enumeration (CPE) information associated with the provided CPE vendor and product values.\n</p>\n\n<div class=\"pin\"><blockquote class=\"callout callout_warn\" theme=\"\ud83d\udea7\"><h3 class=\"callout-heading false\"><span class=\"callout-icon\">\ud83d\udea7</span><p>Restricted Access</p></h3><p>This API endpoint is a premium feature for selected partners.</p></blockquote></div>\n\n<p>\n  CPE vendor and product names come from CPE URIs. These can come from several sources: An <a href=\"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/cve-2014-0160\">entry on NVD</a>, the <a href=\"https://nvd.nist.gov/products/cpe\">CPE dictionary</a> or the results of a previous call to the Inference API.\n</p>\n\n<p>\n  An example from the CPE dictionary looks like this:\n</p>\n\n<pre><code>\n[cpe-item name=\"cpe:/a:microsoft:office:2007\"]\n  [title xml:lang=\"en-US\"]Microsoft Office 2007[/title]\n  [meta:item-metadata nvd-id=\"38081\" status=\"FINAL\" modification-date=\"2008-04-15T23:55:38.437Z\"/]\n[/cpe-item]\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>\n  In this case the CPE URI is \"cpe:/a:microsoft:office:2007\". The cpe_vendor is \"microsoft\", and the cpe_title is \"office\":'\n</p>\n\n<code>\n/v2/application_mappings/find_by_cpe_title?cpe_vendor=microsoft&cpe_title=office\n</code>\n\n<p>Results:</p>\n\n<pre><code>\n{\n  \"cpe_normalized_application_names\": [\n    \"Microsoft Office\",\n    \"Microsoft Office SP3\",\n    \"Microsoft Office Professional\",\n    \"Microsoft Office Service Pack 2 on X86\"\n    ...etc\n  ],\n  \"cpe_mappings\": [\n    {\n      \"cpe_vendor\": \"microsoft\",\n      \"cpe_product\": \"office\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"vendor_binary_information\": [\n    {\n      \"vendor\": \"Microsoft Corporation\",\n      \"product\": \"Microsoft Office\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"vendor\": \"Microsoft Corporation\",\n      \"product\": \"Microsoft\u00ae Office\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"vendor\": \"Microsoft Office\",\n      \"product\": \"Microsoft Office\"\n    },\n    ...etc\n  ],\n  \"cpe_application_names\": [\n    \"Microsoft Office\",\n    \"Microsoft Office 2013 Service Pack 2 on X86\",\n    \"Microsoft Office 2019 on x64\",\n    \"Microsoft Office 2019 on x86\",\n    \"Microsoft Office 2021 Long Term Servicing Channel (LTSC) Edition for MacOS\"\n    ...etc\n  ],\n  \"cpes\": [\n    {\n      \"product_version\": \"2000\",\n      \"cpe_uri\": \"cpe:/a:microsoft:office:2000:sp1\",\n      \"cpe_uri_format\": \"2.2\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"product_version\": \"2021\",\n      \"cpe_uri\": \"cpe:/a:microsoft:office:2021::~~ltsc~macos~~\",\n      \"cpe_uri_format\": \"2.2\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"product_version\": \"2013\",\n      \"cpe_uri\": \"cpe:/a:microsoft:office:2013::~~click-to-run~~x64~\",\n      \"cpe_uri_format\": \"2.2\"\n    }\n    ...etc\n  ]\n}</code></pre>\n          ",
        "operationId": "application_mappings-find_by_cpe_mappings",
        "security": [
          {
            "X-Risk-Token": []
          }
        ],
        "tags": [
          "INFERENCE V2 - Application Mappings"
        ],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "cpe_vendor",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "The specified vendor being requested, extracted from CPE URI.",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "cpe_product",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "The specified product being requested, extracted from CPE URI.",
            "required": true,
